ers-hyderabad-donatte-10-crore-coronavirus-fund-ipl-2020-1665118-2020-04-09|website=indiatoday|author=| date= 9 April 2020|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date= 9 April 2020}}</ref> [[Paytm]] denoted 100 crore.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Paytm collects Rs 100 crore for PM-CARES fund from donors| url=https://m.businesstoday.in/story/coronavirus-paytm-collects-rs-100-crore-for-pm-cares-fund-from-donors/1/400754.html|website=Business Standard|author=| date= 11 April 2020|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date= 11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===PM CARES Fund===\n\nOn 28 March, the [[PM CARES Fund|Prime Minister's Citizen Assistance and Relief in Emergency Situations Fund]] (PM CARES Fund) was set up to provide relief to the affected people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsonair.com/Main-News-Details.aspx?id=384047|title=People urged to donate generously in PM CARES fund; PM Modi says every contribution matters|website=newsonair.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> Several large business groups contributed to the relief fund, including [[Tata Sons]] and [[Sir Ratan Tata Trust|Tata Trusts]] ({{INR}}1,500 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Tata Sons' Rs 1,000 cr top-up takes group coronavirus fund to Rs 1,500 cr - India's biggest |url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/tata-sons-announces-additional-rs-1000-crore-support-towards-coronavirus-fund/story/399506.html |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Business Today}}</ref> [[Wipro]] and [[Azim Premji]] Foundation ({{INR}}1,125 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Azim Premji\u2019s foundation, Wipro commit Rs 1,125 crore as India battles with coronavirus |url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/azim-premjis-foundation-wipro-commit-rs-1125-crore-as-india-battles-with-coronavirus/1916114/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Financial Express}}</ref> [[Reliance Industries]] ({{INR}}500 crore)<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Reliance Industries announces Rs 500 c