s its contribution to Rs 201 crore to fight COVID -19 |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/vedanta-doubles-its-contribution-to-rs-201-crore-to-fight-covid-19/articleshow/74952721.cms?from=mdr |work=The Economic Times |date=2 April 2020}}</ref> ArcelorMittal Nippon Steel India ({{INR}}100 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=COVID-19: Lakshmi Mittal announces contribution of Rs 100 cr to PM CARES Fund |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/covid-19-lakshmi-mittal-announces-contribution-of-rs-100-cr-to-pm-cares-fund-120040100011_1.html |work=Business Standard India |date=1 April 2020}}</ref> [[ITC Limited]] ({{INR}}100 crore)<ref>{{cite web |title=Indian companies contributing to PM-CARES Fund to fight COVID-19 |url=https://www.investindia.gov.in/team-india-blogs/indian-companies-contributing-pm-cares-fund-fight-covid-19 |website=www.investindia.gov.in |language=en}}</ref> and [[Bharti Enterprises]] ({{INR}}100 crore).<ref>{{cite web |title=Bharti Enterprises pledges Rs 100 crore to help government fight against COVID-19 |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/bharti-enterprises-pledges-rs-100-crore-to-help-government-fight-against-covid-1920200406003520/ |website=ANI News |language=en}}</ref>\n\nBeside those above, some well known Indian firms have also contributed like [[Kotak Mahindra Bank]] and [[Uday Kotak]] ({{INR}}50 crore) {{INR}}25 each,<ref>{{cite news |title=Kotak Mahindra Bank, Uday Kotak jointly pledge \u20b950 crore to PM-CARES Fund |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/kotak-mahindra-bank-uday-kotak-jointly-pledge-rs-50-crore-to-pm-cares-fund-11585477616252.html |work=Livemint |date=29 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> [[Asian Paints]] ({{INR}}35 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Asian Paints announces Rs 35 crores contribution to combat Coronavirus outbreak |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/asian-paints-announces-rs-35-crores-contribution-to-combat-coronavirus-out