ival and Awards|Golden Horse Award for Best Actor]]<br />[[Golden Bauhinia Awards|Golden Bauhinia Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| ''[[Hero (2002 film)|Hero]]''\n| Broken Sword\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2003\n| ''[[Infernal Affairs III]]''\n| Chan Wing-yan\n|\n|-\n| ''[[My Lucky Star (2003 film)|My Lucky Star]]''\n| Lai liu po\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Sound of Colors (film)|Sound of Colors]]''\n| Ho Yuk-ming\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2004\n| ''[[Super Model (2004 film)|Super Model]]''\n| Cameo\n|\n|-\n| ''[[2046 (film)|2046]]''\n| Chow Mo-wan\n| [[24th Hong Kong Film Awards|Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor]]<br />[[Golden Bauhinia Awards|Golden Bauhinia Award for Best Actor]]<br />[[Hong Kong Film Critics Society Awards|Hong Kong Film Critics Society Award for Best Actor]]<br/>Nominated\u2014[[Golden Horse Film Festival and Awards|Golden Horse Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Seoul Raiders]]''\n| Agent Lam\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Confession of Pain]]''\n| Detective Lau Ching-hei\n| Nominated\u2014[[26th Hong Kong Film Awards|Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Lust, Caution]]''\n| Mr. Yee\n| [[Golden Horse Film Festival and Awards|Golden Horse Award for Best Actor]]<br />[[2nd Asian Film Awards|Asian Film Awards for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Red Cliff (film)|Red Cliff: Part 1]]''\n| [[Zhou Yu]]\n| Nominated\u2014[[28th Hong Kong Film Awards|Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2009\n| ''[[Red Cliff (film)|Red Cliff: Part 2]]''\n| [[Zhou Yu]]\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Ashes of Time Redux]]''\n| Blind Swordsman\n|\n|-\n||2011\n| ''[[The Great Magician]]''\n| Chang Hsien\n|\n|-\n||2012\n| ''[[The Silent War (film)|The Silent War]]''\n| He Bing\n| Nominated\u2014[[32nd Hong Kong Film Awards|Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2013\n| ''[[The Grandmaster (film)|The Grandmaster]]''\n| [[Ip Man]]\n| Nominated\u2014[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor]]<br />Nominated\u2014[[Golden Horse Film Festival and Awards|Golden Horse Award for Best Actor]]''\n|-\n| ''[[1905 (film)|1905]]''\n| Yan Yunlong\n| Production cancelled February 2013<ref name=\"sankei20130225\">{{cite web|url= http://sankei.jp.msn.com/entertainments/news/130225/ent13022512470019-n1.htm|script-title= ja:\u4e2d\u5805\u6620\u753b\u4f1a\u793e\u306e\u30d7\u30ec\u30ce\u30f3\u30fb\u30a2\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u304c\u7834\u7523\u3000\u5c16\u95a3\u554f\u984c\u306e\u5f71\u97ff\u3067\u30c8\u30cb\u30fc\u30fb\u30ec\u30aa\u30f3\u304c\u51fa\u6f14\u898b\u9001\u308a|trans-title= Film company Prenom H goes bankrupt \u2013 Tony Leung's involvement cancelled due to Senkaku dispute|date= 25 February 2013|work= MSN Sankei News|publisher= The Sankei Shimbun & Sankei Digital|location= Japan|language= Japanese|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130226012117/http://sankei.jp.msn.com/entertainments/news/130225/ent13022512470019-n1.htm|archivedate= 26 February 2013|accessdate= 26 February 2013|url-status= dead|df= dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2016\n| ''Hema Hema: Sing Me a Song While I Wait''\n|Deer / Serene Mask\n|\n|-\n| ''[[See You Tomorrow (2016 film)|See You Tomorrow]]''\n| Chen Mo\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 2018\n| ''[[Monster Hunt 2]]''\n| Tu Sigu\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Europe Raiders]]''\n| Mr Lin\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Theory of Ambitions]]''\n| Nam Kong\n|\n|-\n| 2021\n| ''[[Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings]]''\n| [[Mandarin (character)|Mandarin]]\n| Filming\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''[[The Young Heroes of Shaolin]]''\n| Shaolin monk\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\"| 1982\n| ''[[Demi-Gods and Semi-Devils (1982 TV series)|Demi-Gods and Semi-Devils]]''\n| monk, episode 44\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Legend of Master So]]''\n| waiter\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Manager & Messenger]]''\n| general manager\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Hong Kong '82]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Wut Lik Sap Yat]]''\n| Hung Kwok-choi\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Soldier of Fortune (1982 TV series)|Soldier of Fortune]]''\n| Ying Chi-him\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Emissary (TV series)|The Emissary]]''\n| brother\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 1983\n| ''[[The Superpower]]''\n| Kwok Hak-chung\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Beyond the Rose Garden]]''\n| Tin-yau\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Encounter with Fortune]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Angels and Devils (TV series)|Angels and Devils]]''\n| Kong Ho-man\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 1984\n| ''[[The Clones (TV series)|The Clones]]''\n| Cheung Ka-wai / Chiang Ka-wai\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Duke of Mount Deer (1984 Hong Kong TV series)|The Duke of Mount Deer]]''\n| [[Wei Xiaobao|Wai Siu-bo]]\n|\n|-\n| ''[[It's a Long Way Home]]''\n| Yau Ga-kei\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Police Cadet '84]]''\n| Cheung Wai-kit\n|\n|-\n| ''[[No Regrets for Our Youth (TV series)|No Regrets for Our Youth]]''\n| Frankie\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1985\n| ''[[The Rough Ride]]''\n| Chow Kim-hung\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Police Cadet '85]]''\n| Cheung Wai-kit\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Yang's Saga]]''\n| Yeung Yin-chi (Yeung Chat-long) / [[Lei Gong|Duke of Thunder]]\n|\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''[[New Heavenly Sword and Dragon Sabre]]''\n| [[Zhang Wuji|Cheung Mo-kei]]\n|\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[The Grand Canal (TV series)|The Grand Canal]]''\n| Cheung Sam-long\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 1988\n| ''[[Police Cadet '88]]''\n| Cheung wai-kit\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Behind Silk Curtains]]''\n| Lin Kar-yip\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Everybody's Somebody's Favourite]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Two Most Honorable Knights]]''\n| \"Little Fishie\" Kong Siu-yu\n|\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Ode to Gallantry (1989 TV series)|Ode to Gallantry]]''\n| Shek Po-tin / Shek Chung-yuk\n|\n|}\n\n<ref name=\"two\">{{Cite web |url=http://chinesemov.com/actors/Tony%20Leung%20Chiu.html |title=Tony Leung Chiu-Wai |accessdate=8 April 2010 |publisher=chinesemov.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n*''Raining Night (\u6726\u6727\u591c\u96e8\u88e1)'' (1986)\n*''Who Wants'' (1988)\n*''Love Day by Day'' (1993)\n*''One Life One Heart'' (1994)\n*''Trapped by Love'' (1994)\n*''Day and Night'' (1994)\n*''Cannot Forget'' Collection (1995)\n*''The Past and the Future'' (1995)\n*''Too Affectionate'' (1995)\n*''Tony Leung Greatest Hits'' (June 2000)\n*''In the Mood for Love'' (November 2000)\n*''Wind Sand'' (2004) (reissued January 2006)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n*[[Asian Film Awards]]\n**2008 Best Actor (''[[Lust, Caution]]'')\n*[[2000 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes Film Festival]]\n**2000 [[Best Actor Award (Cannes Film Festival)|Best Actor]] (''In the Mood for Love'')<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\" />\n*[[Golden Horse Film Festival]]\n**2014 Nominated Best Actor (''The Grandmaster'')\n**2007 Best Actor (''Lust, Caution'')\n**2004 Nominated Best Actor (''2046'')\n**2003 Best Actor (''Infernal Affairs'')\n**2000 Nominated Best Actor (''In the Mood for Love'')\n**1994 Best Actor (''Chungking Express'')\n*[[Hong Kong Film Awards]]\n**[[32nd Hong Kong Film Awards|2013 Nominated Best Actor]]''[[The Silent War (film)|(The Silent War)]]''\n**[[28th Hong Kong Film Awards|2009 Nominated Best Actor (''Red Cliff'')]]\n**[[26th Hong Kong Film Awards|2007 Nominated Best Actor (''Confession of Pain'')]]\n**'''[[24th Hong Kong Film Awards|2005 Won Best Actor (''2046'')]]'''\n**'''[[22nd Hong Kong Film Awards|2003 Won Best Actor (''Infernal Affairs'')]]'''\n**'''[[20th Hong Kong Film Awards|2001 Won Best Actor (''In the Mood for Love'')]]'''\n**[[18th Hong Kong Film Awards|1999 Nominated Best Actor (''Longest Nite'')]]\n**'''[[17th Hong Kong Film Awards|1998 Won Best Actor (''Happy Together'')]]\n**'''[[14th Hong Kong Film Awards|1995 Won Best Actor (''Chungking Express'')]]'''\n**[[12th Hong Kong Film Awards|1993 Nominated Best Supporting Actor (''Hard-Boiled'')]]\n**'''[[9th Hong Kong Film Awards|1990 Won Best Supporting Actor (''My Heart Is That Eternal Rose'')]]'''\n**'''[[7th Hong Kong Film Awards|1988 Won Best Supporting Actor (''People's Hero'')]]'''\n**[[6th Hong Kong Film Awards|1987 Nominated Best Actor (''Love Unto Waste'')]]\n(9 Best Actor Nominations, 3 Best Supporting Actor Nominations)\n*[[Golden Bauhinia Awards]]\n**2005 Won Best Actor (''2046'')\n**2003 Won Best Actor (''Infernal Affairs'')\n**1998 Won Best Actor (''Happy Together'')\n*[[Hong Kong Film Critics Society Awards]]\n**2005 Best Actor (''2046'')<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/Sections/Awards/Hong_Kong_Film_Critics_Society_Awards/2005 Hong Kong Film Critics Society Awards 2005] at the Internet Movie Database</ref>\n*Chinese Film Media Awards\n**2000 Won Best Actor (In the Mood for Love)\n*Hong Kong Film Directors' Guild Awards.\n**2014 Won Best Actor (The Grandmaster)\n*Tallinn Black Nights Film Festival\n**2004 Won Best Actor (2046)\n*Iron Elephant Film Awards\n**2007 Won Best Actor (Lust, Caution)\n*Hong Kong Society of Cinematographers (HKSC) Awards\n**2008 Most Charismatic Actor\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote|Tony Leung Chiu Wai|Tony Leung Chiu-wai}}\n{{Commons category|Leung Chiu-Wai, Tony|Tony Leung Chiu-wai}}\n*{{IMDb name|504897|Tony Leung Chiu-wai}}\n*[http://hkmdb.com/db/people/view.mhtml?id=5679&display_set=eng Tony Leung Chiu-wai at the Hong Kong Movie Database]\n*[http://www.lovehkfilm.com/people/leung_chiu_wai.htm Tony Leung Chiu-wai] at [http://www.lovehkfilm.com/ LoveHKFilm.com]\n*[http://www.tonyleung.info/ Tony Leung Chiu-wai fan site]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Tony Leung Chiu-wai\n|list =\n{{Asian Film Award for Best Actor}}\n{{Prix d'interpr\u00e9tation masculine 2000\u20132019}}\n{{Chinese Film Media Awards Best Actor}} \n{{GoldenHorseAwardBestActor}}\n{{Best Actor HKFA}}\n{{Best Supporting Actor HKFA}}\n{{Best Actor HKFCSA}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leung, Tony Chiu-Wai}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Hong Kong male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hong Kong male actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cantopop singers]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong Buddhists]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong male film actors]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong male singers]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong Mandopop singers]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong people of Taishan descent]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong male television actors]]\n[[Category:Cannes Film Festival Award for Best Actor winners]]\n[[Category:Best Actor Asian Film Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Hong Kong film and television actor}}\n{{Distinguish|Tony Leung Ka-fai}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2019}}\n{{chinese name|[[Liang (surname)|Leung]]}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Tony Leung Chiu-wai\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Tony Leung Chiu Wai (Berlin Film Festival 2013) 2 (cropped).jpg\n| image_upright      = \n| landscape          = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = Tony Leung at the 2013 [[Berlin Film Festival]]\n| native_name        = \u6881\u671d\u5049\n| native_name_lang   = zh\n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1962|6|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[British Hong Kong]]\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (enter DEATH date then BIRTH date (e.g., ...|1908|31|8|1967|28|2}} use both this parameter and |birth_date to display the person's date of birth, date of death, and age at death) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       = <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| burial_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Actor, singer\n| years_active      